            "description": "# Login Endpoint\n\n## Overview\n\nThis endpoint authenticates users by validating their credentials (email and password) and returns an access token for subsequent authenticated API requests.\n\n## Request Details\n\n**Endpoint:** `{{base_url}}/auth/login`  \n**Method:** `POST`  \n**Content-Type:** `application/json`\n\n## Request Body Parameters\n\nThe request body must be sent as JSON with the following required fields:\n\n| Parameter | Type | Required | Description |\n| --- | --- | --- | --- |\n| `email` | string | Yes | The user's email address used for authentication |\n| `password` | string | Yes | The user's password (should be securely hashed on the client side) |\n\n### Example Request Body\n\n``` json\n{\n  \"email\": \"email@mail.com\",\n  \"password\": \"hashPasword12@\"\n}\n\n ```\n\n## Response Structure\n\nThe API returns a JSON object with the following structure:\n\n| Field | Type | Description |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| `success` | boolean | Indicates whether the login was successful |\n| `message` | string | A human-readable message describing the result |\n| `data` | object | Contains the authentication data (accessToken and expirationDate) |\n| `data.accessToken` | string | JWT token to be used for authenticating subsequent API requests |\n| `data.expirationDate` | string | The date when the access token expires (ISO 8601 format) |\n| `errors` | null/object | Contains error details if the request fails, null on success |\n\n## Success Response Example\n\n**Status Code:** `200 OK`\n\n``` json\n{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"message\": \"Login sucessfully\",\n  \"data\": {\n    \"accessToken\": \"eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...\",\n    \"expirationDate\": \"2026-03-19\"\n  },\n  \"errors\": null\n}\n\n ```\n\n## Notes\n\n- **Token Storage:** The post-response script automatically saves the `accessToken` to the environment variable `accessToken` for use in subsequent requests.\n    \n- **Token Usage:** Include the access token in the `Authorization` header as a Bearer token for authenticated endpoints: `Authorization: Bearer {accessToken}`\n    \n- **Token Expiration:** Monitor the `expirationDate` field to refresh the token before it expires.\n    \n- **Security:** Always use HTTPS in production to protect credentials during transmission.\n    \n- **Error Handling:** If authentication fails, the `success` field will be `false` and the `errors` field will contain details about the failure."
          },
